g","Greedy","Sorting"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **0-indexed** integer array `nums` and an integer `p`. Find `p` pairs of indices of `nums` such that the **maximum** difference amongst all the pairs is **minimized**. Also, ensure no index appears more than once amongst the `p` pairs.\n\nNote that for a pair of elements at the index `i` and `j`, the difference of this pair is `|nums[i] - nums[j]|`, where `|x|` represents the **absolute** **value** of `x`.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** **maximum** difference among all *`p` *pairs.* We define the maximum of an empty set to be zero.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [10,1,2,7,1,3], p = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: The first pair is formed from the indices 1 and 4, and the second pair is formed from the indices 2 and 5. \nThe maximum difference is max(|nums[1] - nums[4]|, |nums[2] - nums[5]|) = max(0, 1) = 1. Therefore, we return 1.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [4,2,1,2], p = 1\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: Let the indices 1 and 3 form a pair. The difference of that pair is |2 - 2| = 0, which is the minimum we can attain.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `0 <= p <= (nums.length)/2`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Binary Search","Dynamic Programming","Greedy","Sorting"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a **0-indexed** integer array `nums` and an integer `p`. Find `p` pairs of indices of `nums` such that the **maximum** difference amongst all the pairs is **minimized**. Also, ensure no index appears more than once amongst the `p` pairs.\n\nNote that for a pair of elements at the index `i` and `j`, the difference of this pair is `|nums[i] - nums[j]|`, where `|x|` represents the **absolute** **value** of `x`.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** **maximum** difference among all *`p` *pairs.* We define the maximum of an empty set to be zero.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [10,1,2,7,1,3], p = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: The first pair is formed from the indices 1 and 4, and the second pair is formed from the indices 2 and 5. \nThe maximum difference is max(|nums[1] - nums[4]|, |nums[2] - nums[5]|) = max(0, 1) = 1. Therefore, we return 1.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [4,2,1,2], p = 1\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: Let the indices 1 and 3 form a pair. The difference of that pair is |2 - 2| = 0, which is the minimum we can attain.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `0 <= p <= (nums.length)/2`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/minimize-the-maximum-difference-of-pairs/","problemName":"Minimize the Maximum Difference of Pairs","problemNumber":2616,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **0-indexed** integer array `nums` and an integer `p`. Find `p` pairs of indices of `nums` such that the **maximum** difference amongst all the pairs is **minimized**. Also, ensure no index appears more than once amongst the `p` pairs.\n\nNote that for a pair of elements at the index `i` and `j`, the difference of this pair is `|nums[i] - nums[j]|`, where `|x|` represents the **absolute** **value** of `x`.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** **maximum** difference among all *`p` *pairs.* We define the maximum of an empty set to be zero.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [10,1,2,7,1,3], p = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: The first pair is formed from the indices 1 and 4, and the second pair is formed from the indices 2 and 5. \nThe maximum difference is max(|nums[1] - nums[4]|, |nums[2] - nums[5]|) = max(0, 1) = 1. Therefore, we return 1.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [4,2,1,2], p = 1\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: Let the indices 1 and 3 form a pair. The difference of that pair is |2 - 2| = 0, which is the minimum we can attain.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `0 <= p <= (nums.length)/2`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Medium","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given a **0-indexed** integer array `nums` and an integer `p`. Find `p` pairs of indices of `nums` such that the **maximum** difference amongst all the pairs is **minimized**. Also, ensure no index appears more than once amongst the `p` pairs.\n\nNote that for a pair of elements at the index `i` and `j`, the difference of this pair is `|nums[i] - nums[j]|`, where `|x|` represents the **absolute** **value** of `x`.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** **maximum** difference among all *`p` *pairs.* We define the maximum of an empty set to be zero.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [10,1,2,7,1,3], p = 2\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: The first pair is formed from the indices 1 and 4, and the second pair is formed from the indices 2 and 5. \nThe maximum difference is max(|nums[1] - nums[4]|, |nums[2] - nums[5]|) = max(0, 1) = 1. Therefore, we return 1.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [4,2,1,2], p = 1\nOutput: 0\nExplanation: Let the indices 1 and 3 form a pair. The difference of that pair is |2 - 2| = 0, which is the minimum we can attain.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `0 <= p <= (nums.length)/2`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/minimize-the-maximum-difference-of-pairs/","problemName":"Minimize the Maximum Difference of Pairs","problemNumber":2616,"problemSlug":"minimize-the-maximum-difference-of-pairs","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":2616,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":5909,"contentType":"im