ck","Simulation"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a string `s` consisting only of **uppercase** English letters.\n\nYou can apply some operations to this string where, in one operation, you can remove **any** occurrence of one of the substrings `\"AB\"` or `\"CD\"` from `s`.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** possible length of the resulting string that you can obtain*.\n\n**Note** that the string concatenates after removing the substring and could produce new `\"AB\"` or `\"CD\"` substrings.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: s = \"ABFCACDB\"\nOutput: 2\nExplanation: We can do the following operations:\n- Remove the substring \"ABFCACDB\", so s = \"FCACDB\".\n- Remove the substring \"FCACDB\", so s = \"FCAB\".\n- Remove the substring \"FCAB\", so s = \"FC\".\nSo the resulting length of the string is 2.\nIt can be shown that it is the minimum length that we can obtain.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: s = \"ACBBD\"\nOutput: 5\nExplanation: We cannot do any operations on the string so the length remains the same.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= s.length <= 100`\n\n- `s` consists only of uppercase English letters.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["String","Stack","Simulation"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a string `s` consisting only of **uppercase** English letters.\n\nYou can apply some operations to this string where, in one operation, you can remove **any** occurrence of one of the substrings `\"AB\"` or `\"CD\"` from `s`.\n\nReturn *the **minimum** possible length of the resulting string that you can obtain*.\n\n**Note** that the string concatenates after removing the substring and could produce new `\"AB\"` or `\"CD\"` substrings.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: s = \"ABFCACDB\"\nOutput: 2\nExplanation: We